description:
Andersen, an international IT company, invites an experienced Data Analyst to work in the field of Marketing and Advertising.

The project is to provide BI solutions and support internal departments and client teams in their daily reporting work by designing, developing, and testing new requirements and change requests within BI tool stack.

The customer is a German company, part of one of the largest media agency networks in the world. The company is a global leader in marketing, communications and business transformation. Its networks and clients specialize in the following areas: Data and Technology, Analytics and Insights, Research, Content, Media Buying and Business Development. The company works with Disney, Coca-Cola, Maserati, Meta and Google.

Technology stack: Microsoft Power BI/Power Query, SQL, a/b tests, Azure Databricks, Azure Synapse Analytics, Microsoft Azure.

Responsibilities:
• Building and maintaining visually appealing and engaging dashboards/reports for external... customers as well as internal stakeholders using Microsoft Power BI;
• Developing multidimensional semantic layers and BI query objects for end users;
• Collaborating with stakeholders (e.g. Data Solution Managers) to obtain, assess and transform business requirements for dashboard/report creation;
• Coordinating the required data representation/models with the BI Backend Developers;
• Adapting existing dashboards/reports to accommodate changes in source systems and new business requirements;
• Providing second-level support to power users who develop reports on behalf of their departmental colleagues;
• Ensuring appropriate documentation for all development and modifications.

Must-haves:
• Experience as a Data Analyst for 3+ years;
• Experience with SQL, PL/SQL - B/I, Excel;
• Experience with Microsoft Power BI/Power Query;
• Experience with A/B testing;
• Knowledge of and experience with Azure Databricks, Azure Synapse Analytics;
• Experience in Business Intelligence;
• Good presentation and data visualization skills;
• Knowledge of relational and multidimensional database concepts and design;
• Knowledge of data preparation and modeling techniques;
• high level of accuracy, attention to detail;
• Experience in obtaining data from different sources;
• Level of English – from Intermediate.

Nice-to-haves:
• Experience with Microsoft Azure, ETL/ELT pipelines, Microsoft Power Platform;
• Knowledge of media/advertising business.
• Knowledge of OLAP data processing technology (BigQuery/ClickHouse);
• Experience with ETL/ELT pipelines, AirFlow/Luigi/Apache Oozie;
• Experience with Amazon Redshift/Snowflake;
• Experience of organizing training/support.

Reasons why this job would be interesting to you:
• Experience in teamwork with leaders in FinTech, Healthcare, Retail, Telecom, and others. Andersen cooperates with such businesses as Samsung, Siemens, Johnson & Johnson, BNP Paribas, Ryanair, Mercedes, TUI, Verivox, Allianz, T-Systems, etc.;
• The opportunity to change the project and/or develop expertise in an interesting business domain;
• Job conditions – you can work both fully remotely and from the office or can choose a hybrid variant;
• Guarantee of professional, financial, and career growth! The company has introduced systems of mentoring and adaptation for each new employee;
• The opportunity to earn additional up to 1,700 EUR per month by participating in the company's activities;
• Access to the corporate training portal, where the entire knowledge base of the company is collected and which is constantly updated;
• Bright corporate life (parties / pizza days / PlayStation / fruits / coffee / snacks / movies);
• Certification compensation (AWS, PMP, etc);
• Referral program;
• English courses;
• Private health insurance and compensation for sports activities.

Join us

